It’s that time of the year again. But what happened to chestnuts roasting, people dressed like eskimos, santa coming down your chimney and kids looking high up for reindeers on sleighs. Nat king cole said it best, year was 1946 right after WWII. I lived my whole life in New York City and even though I don’t celebrate Christmas, the holiday spirit always put me in a great mood. I miss the days when Toys “R” Us, was the go to place and you actually felt the toys with your bare hands. The truth is, I know the exact answer to why the spirits and the moods were better in the past years. I can sum up it up in one word, “belief”. That’s what people had, nowadays people lack that attribute. It’s that time of the year again where we have to start to believe. As a Mentalist, and Magician, I encourage everyone to use your imaginations during these holidays and create a magical memory for yourself, your families and your friends. Always believe, you’ll be amazed, at what life can give you!  #holidayspirit #believe #believenyc #nycspirit #thattimeahain #christmas #holidays #chestnuts #magic #magician #mentalist #illusionist #miracleshappen #snowdays #nycskyline
